Experimental Economics: Data Workflow

Author
Affiliation

Matteo Ploner

DEM-CEEL, University of Trento

Course Description

The course deals with the design of an experiment in social sciences and the management of the related data workflow . As a take-home assignment, participants are invited to develop their own experimental design and implement the related software.

The following chart illustrates the workflow of the course.

  • Design
    • Methodological aspects of the design of an economic experiments are discussed in the classroom
  • Registration
    • Illustration of the pre-registration process on OSF with specific attention to hypotheses and data analysis
  • Programming
    • Introduction to oTree architecture and examples of experimental apps
  • Data collection
    • Recruitment of participants via Prolific and online deployment on render.com
  • Data organization
    • Collection, organization and documentation of data in R
